			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Name-That-Shifter-43.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-66128" title="Name That Shifter 43" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Name-That-Shifter-43.jpg" alt="" width="626" height="110" /></a></p>
<div id="attachment_66129" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 160px"><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Shifter-No.-43.jpg"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-66129" title="Shifter No. 43" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Shifter-No.-43-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Click to enlarge</p></div>
<p>On Monday we presented this week’s shifter and asked you to identify the make and model of the vehicle from whence it came. Many of you guessed that the shifter belonged to a Chevrolet Citation, which was close. It is in fact from a 1980 Pontiac Phoenix, and the first commenter to correctly identify it was R, who will receive a <a href="http://shop.caranddriver.com/store/hfmedia/en_US/DisplayCategoryProductListPage/categoryID.49796200/parentCategoryID.19556100">Save the Manuals</a> button and sticker as a reward.</p>
<p>The Phoenix pictured here is from our August 1979 issue. The front-drive sedan’s sloping rear profile preceded the Audi A7’s by three decades (it goes without saying that the Audi looks quite a bit better). The Phoenix cost less than $6995 and was powered by a 2.8-liter V-6 engine making a paltry 115 hp.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/1980-Pontiac-Phoenix.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-66338" title="1980 Pontiac Phoenix" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/1980-Pontiac-Phoenix-626x382.jpg" alt="" width="626" height="382" /></a><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/1980-Pontiac-Phoenix-interior.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-66339" title="1980 Pontiac Phoenix interior" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/1980-Pontiac-Phoenix-interior-626x382.jpg" alt="" width="626" height="382" /></a></p>
