			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/mazda_furai_special_edition_carndriver_glamourshot.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-64897" style="border-style: initial; border-color: initial;" title="Mazda Furai C/D Edition" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/mazda_furai_special_edition_carndriver_glamourshot-626x415.jpg" alt="Mazda Furai C/D Edition" width="626" height="415" /></a></p>
<p>As the Facebook fiends among you are already aware, we recently <a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/car-and-driver-and-car-town-join-forces-for-total-facebook-game-domination/">announced a partnership</a> with the game <a href="http://apps.facebook.com/cartown" target="_blank">Car Town</a>. Our first in a series of monthly contests has now concluded, and here are the results!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/September-Car-Town-contest-winner-by-nazerr.jpg"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-66269" title="September Car Town contest winner by nazerr" src="http://blog.caranddriver.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/September-Car-Town-contest-winner-by-nazerr-220x144.jpg" alt="" width="220" height="144" /></a>September&#8217;s challenge was to wrap a Honda Accord in a “Back to School” design. Last week, our editors chose <a href="https://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.10150467721332977.452246.107118047976">their virtual 10Best wraps</a>, awarding each of the designers a special in-game Scion xB. The top entries were then posted to <a href="http://www.facebook.com/media/set/?set=a.10150467721332977.452246.107118047976&amp;type=1#!/caranddriver" target="_blank">the <em>Car and Driver</em> Facebook page</a> for our fans to vote on. After a week at the polls, the fans overwhelmingly &#8220;Liked&#8221; the chalkboard-look wrap by nazerr, who wins a Mazda Furai concept wearing <em>C/D</em> livery. Congratulations!</p>
<p>The next contest begins on October 11 and the theme will be Halloween. Be sure to enter and then check our Facebook page a week later to &#8220;Like&#8221; your favorites.</p>
